# Next.js App Router — Soulspedia Patterns

## Core Rules
- Always App Router (`app/`). Never Pages Router (`pages/`).
- Always use `@/` alias for all imports.
- Framework: Next.js 16, React 19.

---

## Server vs Client Components

### Decision tree
```
Does it use useState, useEffect, useRef, hooks, or browser APIs? → "use client"
Does it handle user events (onClick, onChange)?                  → "use client"
Everything else                                                  → Server Component (no directive)
```

### File naming convention
```
app/page.tsx                    → Server Component (no directive)
app/HomeLanding.client.tsx      → Client Component ("use client" at top)
app/login/LoginPanel.client.tsx → Client Component ("use client" at top)
```

### Composing Server + Client
```tsx
// app/dark-souls/page.tsx — Server Component
import { GameHubLanding } from "@/components/game/GameHubLanding.client";

export default async function DarkSoulsPage() {
  const data = await fetchSomeData(); // server-side fetch
  return <GameHubLanding data={data} />;
}
```
Pass data as props from Server to Client. Never fetch inside Client Components unless the data is user-specific or real-time.

